ARJUN

Hi Rama,

PFB the list of checks that need to be done on the Vlocity Objects. We are still working on Integration procedures and Omniscripts.
We can classify the items in below list optional and mandatory so that they a CICD admin can choose to run Only Mandatory checks or can include optional checks as part of the Code Quality Check.

Accordingly we can define a score against each objects and thus an overall Code Quality score.

We can have a call to walkthrough on the below list.

DataRaptor:
1.	Salesforce Object Validation (Object Visibility, Object Permissions, Field Visibility, Field Permissions refer to the node "%vlocity_namespace%__CheckFieldLevelSecurity__c" in the dataraptor extract)
2.	Presence of "%vlocity_namespace%__SampleInputJSON__c"  node in the DataRaptor extract and it being not null
3.	When Load Raptor, 
a.	then check if all the required fields are being populated
b.	If at least one field is an Upsert Key which is not disabled
4.	If a DataRaptor is used to insert objects like Cases / Incidents / Service Requests / Activities / Opportunities  then Use Assignment Rules flag has to be checked ( viz: when inserting any object with Assignment rules defined / Applicable)
5.	When running the DataRaptor in a Batch Mode (if applicable) then Ignore Errors has to be recommended
6.	When running the DataRaptor in transactional mode, Rollback On Error has to be recommended 
7.	Naming Convention validations (Project recommendations + Vlocity Recommendations)
 
Template
1.	Ensure active version of the template is present.
2.	Run JS validator, HTML Validator and CSS Validator on the template
3.	Is a preview executed for the active version?
4.	Naming Convention validations (Project recommendations + Vlocity Recommendations)
5.	Validate any template references by identifying the tag/attribute: ng-include (all the validation of the template can be applicable to referred template as well)
6.	The Controller Name in the HTML template should match the controller name on the JS of this template
7.	Validate any static resources used
8.	Can restrict the number of lines of comments in the template
9.	Validate the use of any global variables, the use of merge codes for static binding and two-way binding (if recommended at solution level)
10.	Recommend the use of SLDS based on the tags used: Eg: Buttons: slds-button etc
 
Vlocity Card/Console
1.	Is a Data Source set for the Card Layout?
2.	Naming Convention validations (Project recommendations + Vlocity Recommendations)
3.	Validate Vlocity Action used in the card.
4.	Salesforce Object Validation (Object Visibility, Object Permissions, Field Visibility, Field Permissions)
5.	Card and Card Layout template validation
 
Vlocity Action
1.	Is the Vlocity Action active?
2.	Validate the fields: Display On, Open URL in, Link Type, Target URL and URL Parameter (if Target URL contains parameters), Display sequence



 
Thanks
Regards
Arjun Otturu
Mob : +61 469803165
mailto:arjun.otturu@team.telstra.com


