Srujana

Hi Rama,

PFB the list of checks that need to be done on Integration procedures and Omniscripts.

Integration Procedure
1.      Is the IP version active?
2.      Naming Convention validations (Project recommendations + Vlocity Recommendations)
3.      When using DataRaptor Extract Action, if DataRaptor expects a filter, it has to be passed by the IP
4.      When using DataRaptor Post Action, if DataRaptor expects a Payload, it has to be passed by the IP
5.      Run all the IP checks on any IP referenced by the current IP using Integration Procedure Action
6.      When using a Remote Action, the corresponding apex class (if not a managed class) can be validated for the presence of apex test class and code coverage
7.      There should be atleast one response action
8.      For a HTTP Action
a.      The URL has to be registered in Remote Site Settings
b.      If a Named Credential is used, then it has to be validated for a Valid Auth. Provider (if applicable)
c.       Time Out, retries and Error handlers have to be configured based on the solution recommendations
9.      Is a success preview executed at least once ?
 
Omniscript
1.       Is the Omniscript version active?
2.      Naming Convention validations for Omniscript Header and Elements (Project recommendations + Vlocity Recommendations)
3.      Ensure the child Omniscripts embedded and Integration Procedures have an active version.
4.      Is there an active version of templates which are referred in the Omniscript?
5.      To use a PDF Action, an existing fillable PDF must exist in Documents.
6.      All IP checks are valid for Omniscript since IP is a server side version of Omniscript
7.      Based on Solution level Standards validate below
a.      Specific Templates for specific elements
b.      Save Options
c.       Any other configurations like a mandatory salutation page, Summary Page for any order, Validation Required Option to be set to Submit/step/none and Persistent components required on Reusable Omniscripts or Omniscripts
8.      Run all checks for individual type of elements such as DataRaptor, IP or Reusable Omniscript


Thanks,
Srujana Durvasula.

